"    <div id=\"topicTitle\">",
"     Patient information: Having twins (The Basics)",
"    </div>",
"    <a class=\"contributor contributor_credentials\" href=\"./authors-and-editors/patient-information\">",
"     Written by the doctors and editors at UpToDate",
"    </a>",
"    <div id=\"topicText\">",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H600344900\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What are identical twins and how do they happen?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Identical twins happen when 1 egg is fertilized by 1 sperm and then splits (soon after it is fertilized) to form 2 embryos. An &ldquo;embryo&rdquo; is the term doctors use to describe when a baby starts to grow. Each embryo grows into a baby.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Identical twins have all of the same genes. They are the same sex and look very much alike. Identical twins are less common than fraternal twins.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H600344915\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What are fraternal twins and how do they happen?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Fraternal twins happen when 2 different eggs are fertilized by 2 different sperm. Then there are 2 embryos, each of which grows into a baby.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Fraternal twins share some, but not all, of the same genes. They are like any 2 siblings, but just share the same birthday. Fraternal twins can be 2 girls, 2 boys, or a boy and a girl.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H600344930\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What increases a woman&rsquo;s chances of having twins?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Certain things increase a woman&rsquo;s chances of having twins. These include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Being in her 30s or older",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Taking medicine to help get pregnant",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Having a procedure called &ldquo;in vitro fertilization&rdquo; (also called &ldquo;IVF&rdquo;) to help get pregnant",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Her race &ndash; Twins are more common in black women than in Asian or white women.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Having a family history of twins",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      These things increase a woman&rsquo;s chances of having fraternal twins only, not identical twins.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H600344945\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How does my doctor or midwife know that I&rsquo;m having twins?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;When your doctor or midwife examines you, he or she will feel the size of your uterus (",
"      <a class=\"graphic graphic_figure graphicRef82935 \" href=\"UTD.htm?7/20/7495\">",
"       figure 1",
"      </a>",
"      ). Women who are having twins usually have a uterus that is bigger than expected, given their due date. Also, early in pregnancy, your doctor or midwife will probably do a test called an ultrasound. An ultrasound uses sound waves to create pictures of the inside of your body. This test shows how many babies are in your uterus.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H600344977\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Will I need special prenatal care?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Yes. Women who are pregnant with twins need special prenatal care. They will see their doctor or midwife more often. They will also have frequent ultrasounds to check how their babies are growing. Later on in pregnancy, they might have other tests to check their babies&rsquo; health.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H600344992\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What should I know about having twins?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Having twins is a bit different than having only 1 baby. Your doctor or midwife will talk with you about how much weight you should gain and how active you should be.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      He or she will also talk with you about problems that are more likely to happen when a woman is pregnant with twins. The most common problem is that the babies will be born too early, before 37 weeks of pregnancy (3 or more weeks before the due date). Doctors use the term &ldquo;premature&rdquo; or &ldquo;preterm&rdquo; for babies who are born too early.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Being born too early is sometimes a problem. Preterm babies are more likely to be smaller and need to stay in the hospital for longer after birth. They are also more likely to have medical problems, such as breathing problems.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Women who are carrying twins are also more likely to get high blood pressure during pregnancy.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H600345007\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How will I deliver my babies?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;It depends on the position of the babies in your uterus, your health, and your babies&rsquo; health. If you and your babies are healthy and the first baby is coming head first, you might be able to deliver your babies vaginally. If not, the doctor will do surgery called a c-section to get the babies out.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H600345022\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How do I know if my twins are identical or fraternal?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Twins of the opposite sex are always fraternal. Twins of the same sex can be fraternal or identical.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      If your twins are the same sex, your doctor or midwife might be able to tell if they are identical by checking your placenta. (The placenta is the organ inside a pregnant woman&rsquo;s uterus that brings a baby nutrients and oxygen, and carries away waste.) Sometimes, the only way to tell if twins are identical is by doing blood tests.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H600345039\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Can I breastfeed my babies?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;If you would like to. Most women make enough milk to breastfeed twins. If your babies are born too early, you might need to pump and store your breast milk until your babies are able to drink it.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      You will probably want to work with a breastfeeding expert, called a &ldquo;lactation consultant.&rdquo; That way, you can find a schedule and way of breastfeeding that works best for you and your babies.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H600345054\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What if I am having a tough time taking care of my babies?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;If you are having a tough time, try to get some help. Taking care of twins can be tiring and stressful. You might want to ask friends or relatives to help you. Many parents also find it helpful to join a support group for parents of twins. That way, they can talk to others in the same situation.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H600345069\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       More on this topic",
"      </span>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
